OL,3,CWhere can you see the Northern Lights
OL,4,Ctonight?
OL,6,FWhat's the science behind the Northern
OL,7,FLights?
OL,9,FCharged particles from the sun,
OL,10,Fprimarily electrons and protons,
OL,11,Fcollide with gases in the Earth's
OL,12,Fatmosphere, typically oxygen and
OL,13,Fnitrogen.
OL,15,FThese collisions emit light at various
OL,16,Fwavelengths, creating vibrant displays
OL,17,Fof colour in the sky, often appearing
OL,18,Fas curtains, arcs, or bands of light.
